field.value: Still sounding wishy-washy? Well, consider the charitable aspects: LMFF (the name comes from [Caroline] and her husband's nickname for their young daughter, Isabella) was inspired to help the children in the favelas after her husband returned from Rio with tales of hardship and horror. "When we saw how beautiful the ethnic jewellery was we thought we could help them to trade in a beneficial way. People love the stuff." LMFF wants to expand her business - thereby expanding the horizons of street kids in Rio. If that isn't good karma, then I don't know what is.

field.value: [Corrigan Close] is a new private cobblestone mews developed by John Emery of Fairmont Properties Corporation. The address was formerly 40 South Drive, a 120-by-210-foot lot with a 10,000-square- foot mansion that was built in 1910 by Fred Corrigan, chairman of General Steel Wares. Mr. Emery has divided the abode into three freehold Georgian-style units and added two detached homes to the lot. While haggling with the city for zoning to allow for the subdivision, Mr. Emery rented portions of the house to opera singer Maureen Forrester and television personality Dini Petty.
